India, U.S. to Boost Counter-Terror, Fake Currency Cooperation

-- B y   B i b h u d a t t a   P r a d h a n
-- 
2011-05-27T12:53:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/india-u-s-to-boost-counter-terror-fake-currency-cooperation.html
The U.S. and  India  will increase
counter-terrorism cooperation and share more information to
tackle counterfeit currency and the illegal transfer of funds,
top security officials said after meetings today.  U.S. Homeland Security Secretary Janet Napolitano met her
Indian counterpart, Home Minister Palaniappan Chidambaram, in
 New Delhi . The two countries will build their capacities to stem
the narcotics trade and other transnational crime, they said in
a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bibhudatta Pradhan in New Delhi at 
 bpradhan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hari Govind at 
 hgovind@bloomberg.net  